{
  "texts": [
    "We may note that mini-BAL, characterised by a small level of UV absorption, and narrow absorption line quasars, characterised by absorption width with FWHM < 500 km s -1, generally show different X-ray properties (Hamann et al. 2013; Chartas et al. 2021).",
    "Schechter and Wambsganss (2002) showed this for a single κ, γ combination.",
    "This result was later extended to the entire parameter space byVernardos et al. (2014).",
    "For the accretion disc, Guerras et al. (2020) find that at least 4 measurements (or 4 pairs of images) should be used to obtain reliable estimations.",
    "Although not explicitly studied, something similar probably holds for measuring κ * too."
  ]
}